## Best Practices

### Component Composition

```tsx
// Good: Compose shadcn components
export function ScoreInput({ value, onChange }: Props) {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
      <Button variant="outline" size="icon" onClick={() => onChange(value - 1)}>
        <Minus className="h-4 w-4" />
      </Button>
      <Input
        type="number"
        value={value}
        className="w-16 text-center"
        readOnly
      />
      <Button variant="outline" size="icon" onClick={() => onChange(value + 1)}>
        <Plus className="h-4 w-4" />
      </Button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Form Patterns

```tsx
// Use shadcn Form with react-hook-form
<Form {...form}>
  <FormField
    control={form.control}
    name="score"
    render={({ field }) => (
      <FormItem>
        <FormLabel>Score</FormLabel>
        <FormControl>
          <Input type="number" {...field} />
        </FormControl>
        <FormMessage />
      </FormItem>
    )}
  />
</Form>
```

### Accessibility

Shadcn uses Radix primitives which handle:
- Keyboard navigation
- Focus management
- ARIA attributes
- Screen reader support

**You still need to:**
- Provide meaningful labels
- Ensure color contrast
- Test with keyboard

